; Oxford Nanopore direct cDNA oligo signatures for internal-fragment/concatemer review.
; Source: ONT Ligation sequencing V14 - Direct cDNA sequencing (SQK-LSK114),
; protocol DCS_9187_v114_revK_24Feb2026 / community protocol mirror.
; Sequences are written as plain nucleotide/IUPAC text for matching only.
; The strand-switching primer contains terminal mGmGmG in the protocol; here it
; is represented as GGG for adapter-signature detection.
; The poly(T) VN primer is stored without the terminal degenerate `VN` tail for
; similarity search. Those two anchored positions are intentionally ignored in
; the default matching file because the upstream primer body is already highly
; specific and `V` would otherwise exclude `T` rather than behaving like a
; fully ignorable anchor. For the anchored-primer semantics itself, see EURx
; E0106 "Anchored Oligo(dT)20 VN Primers".
;
; FASTA header metadata currently understood by GENtle:
;   internal_scan=false   -> do not use this signature for internal-read scans
;
; If your dataset used an older ONT cDNA kit, replace or supplement these
; records with the kit-specific oligos from the corresponding ONT document.

>sqk_lsk114_vn_primer role=poly_t_anchored internal_scan=false
ACTTGCCTGTCGCTCTATCTTCTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTT
>sqk_lsk114_strand_switching_primer role=strand_switch_primer
TTTCTGTTGGTGCTGATATTGCTGGG
>sqk_lsk114_pr2_primer role=second_strand_primer
TTTCTGTTGGTGCTGATATTGC
